|    ## Creating client side validation form                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |
|    When we enter data in a form, the browser and/or the web server will check to see that the data is in the correct format and within the constraints set by the application.                                                                                                                                                             |  
|    There are two types of form validation as follows"                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |
|    (i) Client side - means data from frontend through a form is send correctly to the backend, following all validations rules.                                                                                                                                                                                                            |
    (ii) Server side - means data fetched by client through form should be saved correctly into database and correct schema is followed. Also errors are handled properly.
    (i)For handling client side form validation we can set all fields as required. But by using required it will follow browser rules means chrome can show different results and safari can show other results.
       to avoid this and mantain same results in all types of browsers we will use "BootStrap" classes which  set css standardized result.
       BootStrap --> Forms --> validation -->add class="needs-validation" and field "novalidate"--> also add JS logic into (public-->js-->script.js)-->Add the "script.js" file into boilerplate  "<script src="/js/script.js"></script>"
    ## Adding Success and Failure Text 
    Means while filling any form, when we fill value of any field is it success or failure.Success means okay text and follows Validation rules ,it will display in green color,use "valid-feedback" to implement this.Failure means Validation rules are not followed, it will display red in color,use "invalid-feedback" to implement this.
    ## Maintaining Server side validation.
    First we tried to handle it by adding "Error Handling Middleware" at bottom of code and putting "Create Route" code into "try-catch" block.
    But there is better way to handle this ,by using "wrapAsync".
    We will add new folder"utils" , in which we will add code of wrapAsync into "wrapAsync.js" file.And then replacing "try-catch" block by just adding "wrapAsync" before word async.
    Now, even if we enter invalid information , we will be get error on browser but server will not get crash.Make all async functions "wrapAsync"
    ## using ExpressError for "Error Handling"
    In above we sent same type of error. But by ExpressError we can send custom error including status code and message of exact error.
    utils --> ExpressError.js .This file will contain ExpressError class of which we can make instances later wherever needed.Also we should require it in "app.js" file.
    to create common route that will throw "Page not found" error whenever we try to search route other than existing ones.

  "  app.use((req, res, next) => {
    next(new ExpressError(404, "Page Not Found!"));
});
app.use((err,req,res,next) => {
    let {statusCode=500, message="Something went wrong!"} = err;
    res.status(statusCode).send(message);
}); "
