  - To check if user is logged in or not we will use Express static function "isAuthenticate()".As to perform CRUD operations on listings   we should be loggged in first.So will need to specify "isAuthenticate()" function in each route.
    Instead of it we will write code once is "middleware.js" file.
  - Making "/logout" route using passport's "req.logout" method
  - Displayed Signup, Login and Logout options in navbar by "navbar.js" using bootstrap classes
  - Adding functionality such that if user is loggedIn he can see only "logout" option and if not login he will see "Signup" and "Login" options.
  - Up till now we observe that once we signup we also need to login afterwards.But when we use other websites we can see that once we signup, we automatically get login.
    to implement this functionality we will use "req.login" method of passport.which automatically get triggered once we signup.
  - as when we try to perform CRUD operations on listings website first tells to login , and once we login it redirects us to "/listings" instead of that CRUD operation page , which causes unconvenience to users .
    to avoid this we try to save the path user tried to access before login , sothat one user will login we can direct him to that previous path.
    As "req.session" has access of path we try t access even if we unable to get the results(page not found error) req.session saves the path.
    So we will first featch the Url from session object as "req.session.originalUrl" and then saves as follows " req.session.redirectUrl = req.originalUrl;"
    But to make this url accessible everywhere we need to store it in res.local variable , code of which had included in "middleware.js" as "saveRedirectUrl" middleware. And then add this same middleware into "/login" route.
  - There is another loophole: whwn usertry to login first instead of CRUD operations,it should be redirected to "/listings" but he can't. Because for "res.redirect(res.locals.redirectUrl)" value is undefined .
    So solve this we added following logic
    " let redirectUrl = res.locals.redirectUrl || "/listings";
        res.redirect(redirectUrl); "   

