## Upload image
Problems occur while uploading images as follows:
1.till now sending raw data to backend is possible but sending any document is not possible because we send urlencoded data.
2.As mongodb stores BSON type of data, which includes size limit to store documents.
Solution as follows
a. making form capable of sending files
b. use third party service to store files , these third party service will provide URL/Link of stored image
c. save the URL/Link in mongodb
- Manipulating form
  we will try to change datatype from urlencoded to "multipart/form-data" by adding line  "enctype="multipart/form-data" into "new.ejs" file in form component.
Make input type of "Upload Listing Image" as "type='file'" instead of "text".
To parse "multipart/form-data" we will use "multer" npm package.Add code lines in "routes-->listing.js" as follows:
" const multer  = require('multer')
const upload = multer({ dest: 'uploads/' })  "
Add following route in "listing.js" 
" .post( upload.single('listing[image]'),(req,res)=> {
    res.send(req.file);
});  "
it means when post request goes line "upload.single('listing[image]')"  saves uploaded single image into uploads folder.  " res.send(req.file);" is used req.file is object like req.body which stores information related to file.
